#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:104
msgid "Flat description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:106
msgid ""
"A root node is created and it is the parent of all the nodes. This "
"description is the simplest one and it is supposed to give to user space a "
"flat representation of all the devices supporting the power limitation "
"without any power limitation distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:112
msgid "Hierarchical description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:114
msgid ""
"The different devices supporting the power limitation are represented "
"hierarchically. There is one root node, all intermediate nodes are grouping "
"the child nodes which can be intermediate nodes also or real devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:119
msgid ""
"The intermediate nodes aggregate the power information and allows to set the "
"power limit given the weight of the nodes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:123
msgid "User space API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:125
msgid ""
"As stated in the overview, the DTPM framework is built on top of the "
"powercap framework. Thus the sysfs interface is the same, please refer to "
"the powercap documentation for further details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:129
msgid ""
"power_uw: Instantaneous power consumption. If the node is an intermediate "
"node, then the power consumption will be the sum of all children power "
"consumption."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:133
msgid ""
"max_power_range_uw: The power range resulting of the maximum power minus the "
"minimum power."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:136
msgid ""
"name: The name of the node. This is implementation dependent. Even if it is "
"not recommended for the user space, several nodes can have the same name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:140
msgid "constraint_X_name: The name of the constraint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:142
msgid ""
"constraint_X_max_power_uw: The maximum power limit to be applicable to the "
"node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:145
msgid ""
"constraint_X_power_limit_uw: The power limit to be applied to the node. If "
"the value contained in constraint_X_max_power_uw is set, the constraint will "
"be removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:149
msgid ""
"constraint_X_time_window_us: The meaning of this file will depend on the "
"constraint number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:153
msgid "Constraints"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:155
msgid ""
"Constraint 0: The power limitation is immediately applied, without "
"limitation in time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:159
msgid "Kernel API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:164
msgid ""
"The DTPM framework has no power limiting backend support. It is generic and "
"provides a set of API to let the different drivers to implement the backend "
"part for the power limitation and create the power constraints tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:169
msgid ""
"It is up to the platform to provide the initialization function to allocate "
"and link the different nodes of the tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../power/powercap/dtpm.rst:172
msgid ""
"A special macro has the role of declaring a node and the corresponding "
"initialization function via a description structure. This one contains an "
"optional parent field allowing to hook different devices to an already "
"existing tree at boot time."
msgstr ""

